title: On some results of the measurement of the angular distribution of separated gamma-ray production cross section from reaction (n,x+gamma) for V-51 induced by 14.9 MeV neutrons

x4freetext: On some results of the measurement of the angular
distribution of separated gamma-ray production cross
section from reaction (n,x+gamma) for V-51 induced by
14.9 MeV neutrons

x4codes.hlp: Beijing Normal Univ., Beijing, China, People`s Rep.

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Chinese report to the I.N.D.C., No.011, p.165 (1988)

x4freetext: Cylindrical vanadium sample, purity=99.9%,
diameter=3 cm, length=3 cm, weight=130 grams.

x4codes.hlp: Beijing Normal Univ., Beijing, China, People`s Rep.

x4freetext: 400 KV pulsed Cockcroft-Walt. accelerator
300 keV deuteron on T-Ti target, average neutron
intensity about 5.0 x 10**8 neutrons/sec.
A 110.7 cm3 Ge-Li detector with resolution 2.0
keV for 1332.5 keV gamma-ray of Co-60 was used for
gamma-ray measurement.
The absolute efficiency of the detector was calibrated
using a series of standard gamma-ray sources.
The neutron fluence was determined by
associated alpha-particle counting with a Au-Si
surface barrier detector
Corrections were applied for
. neutron fluence attenuation in sample
. multi-scattering of elastic neutrons in sample
. multi-scattering of inelastic neutrons in sample
. gamma-ray self-absorption in sample
. anisotropy of neutron source
. absorption of neutrons by target backing and cooling
water
. neutron source size
Main error sources are as follows:
4.0%    for determination of neutron fluence
2.5-3.0% for absolute efficiency of
Ge(Li)detector in 200 keV to 4 MeV gamma energy range
The minimal total uncertainty of differential cross
sections about 5.0% for the largest gamma peak
Data taken from Table 3 of
LQC.-All previous data and data-err in all subentry
were multiplied with a factor 0.80896 according to the
authors opinion.
